        "content": "<p>I know that <code>x ~ a ++ y</code> and that <code>y ~ b ++ c</code> and I want to derive that <code>x ~ a ++ b ++ c</code>.</p>\n<p>In Coq I would rewrite the second equation in the first, but how to do that in Lean?</p>",
        "id": 477005475,
        "sender_full_name": "Leo Stefanesco",
        "timestamp": 1729003281
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"644391\">@loogle</span> List.Perm, HAppend</p>",
        "id": 477006781,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1729003632
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"shrug\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f937\" role=\"img\" title=\"shrug\">:shrug:</span> nothing found</p>",
        "id": 477006786,
        "sender_full_name": "loogle",
        "timestamp": 1729003633
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=List.Perm.append_left#doc\">docs#List.Perm.append_left</a> to get <code>a ++ y ~ a ++ b ++ c</code>, and then use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=List.Perm.trans#doc\">docs#List.Perm.trans</a></p>",
        "id": 477007072,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1729003703
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Alternatively, you can work with Multisets instead, such that permutation is equality, and then rewriting will work</p>",
        "id": 477007195,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1729003741
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thank you!</p>",
